<subSubSection id="4DE32F20633E561B222D0BC0E8382C77" type="description">
<paragraph id="47EA17B7F12285AC882F53331097EBAB" pageNumber="388">Worker: Length 2.5-2.7 mm. - A distinctly paler variety. The color is a pale grayish ferruginous compared with the dark brown of the typical form. The mesonotal and especially the gastric carinae are more distinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8CCC3835D3544D631B009AAFA46858E" lastPageNumber="389" pageNumber="388">
Female (dealate): Length 3.3 mm. - Color and sculpture 
<pageStartToken id="6A439A129EE476358D58331BE016B7A7" pageNumber="389">as</pageStartToken>
in the worker. Pale ferruginous compared with rich dark brown in dealate females of the typical form.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
